article.headline: San Diego 90, Campbell 81
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Nick Lewis scored 16 points, all in the second half, to lead five players in double figures in San Diego's 90-81 season-opening win over Campbell on Friday. Lewis went 5-of-7 in the second period, including 2-of-2 threes and 4-of-5 from the line. Gyno Pomare added 15 points and 10 rebounds, and Ross DeRogatis also had 15 points. Corey Belser and Brandon Johnson scored 14 each for the Toreros (1-0). San Diego shot 59 percent (16-27) from the floor in the second half, 54 percent (31-57) for the game. That offset 30 turnovers that Campbell converted into 29 points. Maurice Latham led the Camels (0-1) with 18 points, while Reggie Bishop came off the bench to add a career-high 16, Eric Smith had 15, and Diego Aguiar and J'Quincy Jones each added 10. Campbell shot just 39 percent (26-67) for the night. Campbell used a 10-0 run early in the first half to jump to a 14-10 lead. USD answered with its own 10-0 spurt and never trailed again, holding a 44-36 advantage at halftime. Pomare's jumper with 13:04 remaining gave the Toreros their largest lead of the game at 61-47.
